Class IPLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.server.commons.geolocation.IPLocation

    Class containing location information obtained for a given IP address

        See Also:

      • mLatitude

        protected Double mLatitude
        The approximate latitude of the location associated with the IP address. This value is not precise and should not be used to identify a particular address or household.

      • mLongitude

        protected Double mLongitude
        The approximate longitude of the location associated with the IP address. This value is not precise and should not be used to identify a particular address or household.

      • mPostalCode

        protected String mPostalCode
        The postal code of the location. Postal codes are not available for all countries. In some countries, this will only contain part of the postal code.

      • mSubdivisionCodes

        protected List<String> mSubdivisionCodes
        List of subdivisions where location is likely to be. A subdivision is a tring of up to three characters long defining a subdivision (i.e. district, province, autonomous community, region, etc). Order of subdivision codes is the same as subdivisions' names.
        See Also:
        http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2

      • mSubdivisionNames

        protected List<String> mSubdivisionNames
        List of subdivisions' names where location is likely to be. Order of subdivision names is the same as subdivisions' codes.

      • mRegisteredCountryCode

        protected String mRegisteredCountryCode
        Two-character ISO 3166-1 alpha code for the country where the ISP has registered a given IP block. This might differ the actual user's country.

      • mRegisteredCountryName

        protected String mRegisteredCountryName

      • mDomain

        protected String mDomain
        The second level domain associated with the IP address. This will be something like "example.com" or "example.co.uk", not "foo.example.com"

        public String getCountryName()

      • getCountryName

        Returns:
